<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 17 at 4:15AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Dense fog in the Helena valley this morning...
Dense fog has developed in the Helena valley. The fog will reduce
visibility below a quarter of mile at times. The fog will begin to
dissipate by late morning.
Those traveling this morning in the Helena valley should be
prepared for poor visibility because of the fog, and slippery
roadways because of the overnight snowfall.</description>
